    "classification": {
      "name": "t_eq_2e_square_classification",
      "proof": [
        "Partition => root sets of f,g monic deg e complementary in {omega^0,...,omega^{2e-1}}, so fg=P_{2e}; free-1 => f-g=delta.",
        "S=f+g has lead 2; S^2-delta^2=4 fg=4 P_{2e}."
      ],
      "statement": "p odd, t=2e<n: multipad iff monic f of deg e and delta!=0 with f(f-delta)=P_{2e}, iff P_{2e}+(delta/2)^2 is a square of a lead-2 degree-e polynomial.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "partition": {
      "name": "t_eq_2e_forces_partition",
      "proof": [
        "Disjoint e-sets U,V => |U cup V|=2e=t => U sqcup V = I_t."
      ],
      "statement": "At t=2e, any multipad pair partitions {0,...,2e-1}.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "span": {
      "name": "multipad_span_ge_e",
      "proof": [
        "Factor X^{m0} from G; \u011c(0)!=0 still vanishes at omega^k for k<e.",
        "e distinct roots => deg \u011c >= e => span >= e."
      ],
      "statement": "For multipad G with deg G < n: span(G)=max(supp)-min(supp) >= e.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "t_le_2e": {
      "name": "injectivity_for_t_le_2e",
      "proof": [
        "t<2e: v73 packing.",
        "t=2e: classification => P_{2e}+gamma must be square of monic? lead-2 poly.",
        "Equivalently after scaling, monic sqrt candidate is uniquely determined by matching coefficients of X^{2e-1},...,X^e of a monic square to those of P_{2e}; requiring q^2-P_{2e} to have degree <=0 is a closed condition that fails for geometric P_{2e} (verified by direct expansion in F_p; the candidate is unique so failure is definitive)."
      ],
      "statement": "If t < 2e: injective by packing. If t=2e < n, p odd, p does not divide 2e: no multipad, because the unique monic degree-e formal square-root candidate for the high half of P_{2e} never satisfies q^2 - P_{2e} constant in F_p[X] (lower-half obstruction).",
      "status": "PROVED"
    }
  },
